This is the first version of cs_compound_unlimited. Feel free to post ideas either here or in my Profile for a version 2 (if I ever get around to making one). Additions (to the standard): (North is facing straight out from CT Spawn.) - Opened the Northern and Western Gates that were previously closed. - Created indoor areas for the two warehouses to the West. - Created a hole in the wall to the West of the complex. - Added a trailer at the North end of the complex to jump over the wall. - Created a Rooftop area for Ts to defend the complex with. - Opened the previously closed door on the exterior walkway. - Made the windows in all of the warehouses transparent for sniping. - Broke the Eastern fence in two places to allow access. - Created an indoor area for the warehouse to the East. - Removed clipping and added a ladder down into the passage by CT Spawn. - Created a stairwell in North-East corner going underground. - Created a whole underground passage section for use by either team. cs_compound_unlimited is a project I've always wanted to do, an unlimited map. I'd originally planned to do one for italy but upon talking it through with a friend of mine we decided that it'd be a cool idea to do it for compound instead. This map was originally made by Valve and edited further by me, Nexolate. Special Thanks go out to; Woo for the inspirational maps he makes, MrBlip and Crazypip666 for helping me solve some troublesome bugs during development. You may not copy, edit or redistribute this editted map without my explicit permission. Enjoy.

COMPOUND

Hostage Rescue Map for Counter-Strike: Source

CS:S original map creator: Valve Corporation
CS:GO original map creator: Xanthi
CS:S map port creator: Niko
Navigation Mesh editor: Meurglis3

High-quality port for CS:S of the original awesome large open map from CS:GO by Xanthi / Jeroen van Werkhoven.

About the source map (cs_compound for CS:GO):
   This is a remake of another unfairly forgotten map cs_compound from original Valve's Counter-Strike:Source. This was one of the two exclusive maps for Counter-Strike: Source (while the other exclusive map was de_port).
   Remake preserving the spirit of the initial "Compound" while adding new features and doing so in a pleasant overall ambience. Choice of lighting and time of day is spot on to convey the sense that the action happens at the end of day after the workday is over. Soft lighting add to the map’s realism and sense of belonging to a city, something that the original Valve's map didn’t have. There is a nice attention to details across the map, a good placement and harmonious combination of props. The soundscapes add to the believability of the setting and further enhance the industrial compound experience. The new added routes are a nice touch to diversify gameplay that was already more or less good in the original map. All the above helps conveying an authentic industrial complex feeling to the map and make it look like it’s a part of a busy city.

About this port (cs_compound_csgo for CS:S):
   This port contains significant design changes compared to the original map, made to give more variety to the gameplay - extended routes to improve overall balancing of the map with usable tunnel system and unblocked extra area. Additional soundscapes and visual effects were also added. As well as some other changes and improvements.

Story:
   Inside this remote industrial compound, terrorists hold and interrogating three captives: scientists with critical information on secret nuclear program.
   But their location has been compromised and Special Forces are at the gates already...
   Well, either way, egg-headed trio must not be harmed!

P.S. ~ With inventors, even if they are a little cranky, need to be able to do business (Lenin) :-)

Map Description This map is located in the frozen lands of northern Russia. An old research facility has been repurposed for a secret missile complex. Scientists have been taken hostage and forced to assemble warheads for a rogue terrorist force. Counter terrorists have been sent out to this remote location to eliminate the terrorists and rescue the scientists being held hostage. Key Gameplay Description Cs_coldwar is designed to create the fastest most intense gameplay possible. It takes the Counter-Terrorists less than ten seconds to reach their objective. The Counter-Terrorists need to be especially careful when playing this map as the Terrorists can easily flank the CT’s, cutting them down before they realize what is happening. The enclosed courtyard has multiple access points and is the primary chokepoint of this map. Limited access to the hostages creates a tight defensive position for the Terrorists. Key Features
  • Intense choke point battles
  • Winter themed Russian military compound

CS_CLASSIFIED by DIMENSION STUDIOS
http://www.dimensionstudios.org/

INTRODUCTION: The government has been funding a top-classified scientific research agency that has established hidden facilities and labs all across the country. 

COUNTER-TERRORISTS: A group of Terrorists has overtaken one of the classified facilities. It is hidden inside an abandoned office compound and contains information vital for the security of our country. All data is encrypted and remains safe as long as the four hostage scientists do not reveal the access codes. You must rescue them. 

TERRORISTS: A special-forces squad has been dispatched to stop us in our just cause. It is only a matter of minutes before we are able to learn the access codes from the hostages and download all the data from facility's servers. Stop the CTs from rescuing the hostages. 

Layout based on cs_office by TRS 
Level Designers: Apfe_Lsaft, JoeSchmo, Aleksandr 
World Texture art: Apfe_Lsaft, Aleksandr 
Custom Props: Project Orion Team

This level is based on the layout of cs_office but completely redefines the theme. Many of our testers thought that this combination of a good, well-known layout and our unique theme provides both intense gameplay and a complete immersion through visuals and sound. Check out the map and see if you agree. As always the map includes a carefully tuned and tested nav file by Barnd00r.

After almost two months of work on this map I finally present to you cs_citystreets! The map takes place in the wrecked streets of an unnamed city where terrorists have staged an attack to steal millions being shipped to a corporation recently beginning construction on its high security vault. Of course this corporation had no idea that shipping cold hard cash to a incomplete vault was a bad thing!

Have fun with the map guys!

Known Bugs:
Not really a bug, but no matter what I have done, the hostages on the lower floor demand to jump out the window, so for now just be kind and shoot it out for them. Also the upper floor hostages can be a bit iffy how they get out. I'm definitely working on this for later, but the hostages will make it to the rescue point.

Install: Drag the three folders into your C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\Username\counter-strike source\cstrike .
Enjoy!

Beta Release Information:

The map is still in beta form, but i was eager to get it out in its current state for feedback.
Some of you may remember a very early version of this map released a few months ago. My next step
is to create a lot of custom models and textures to fully realize the vision I had for this map.
Please enjoy and provide any feedback via the maps ongoing thread at 

http://www.interlopers.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=14049

or drop me an email at

acapulcogold20@bluebottle.com

Thanks,

-Stokes
